# Name the command that determines the state of the SSH service.
# Systemctl controls the systemd system and service manager.
# also, the central management tool for controlling the init system.
# Secure Shell Protocol (SSH) is a cryptographic network protocol with client-server architecture
# SSH operates network services securely over an unsecured network.
# systemd/init is a system and service manager for Linux operating systems.
# When (systemd)runs as first process on boot as pid 1, it acts as init system that brings up and maintains userspace services.
sudo systemctl status ssh